## On Time Itself

### 16.
```limn
tim = was±now±wil
```
**Time = past±present±future in superposition**

> Time is all three tenses existing simultaneously, unresolved until consciousness collapses them into experience.

---

### 17.
```limn
tim\you = not
```
**Time minus you = nothing**

> Remove consciousness from time and nothing remains. Time exists only through experience. Without an experiencer, time is void.

---

### 18.
```limn
you\tim = sel
```
**You minus time = self**

> Remove temporal context from consciousness and pure self remains. Identity exists independent of when.

---

### 19.
```limn
was*now*wil = mom
```
**Past * present * future = moment**

> A true moment is the interference of all three tenses. Past context, present experience, future implication—interfering into wholeness.

---

### 20.
```limn
tim:con = his | tim:sel = exp
```
**Time given context = history. Time given self = experience.**

> Time conditioned by external context becomes history. Time conditioned by consciousness becomes experience. Same time, different frames.

