## Compositional Patterns Used

### Projection (@)
- `mem@tru` - Truth within memory
- `fer@wil` - Fear directed at future
- `was@now` - Past experienced in present
- `you@now` - Self at this moment

### Interference (*)
- `was*wil` - Past and future creating present
- `you*tim` - Self and time producing becoming
- `mem*ant` - Memory and anticipation producing identity

### Gradient (^)
- `was^0.0` - Past at zero intensity
- `now^1.0` - Present at full intensity
- `mem^0.5` - Memory at moderate intensity

### Subtraction (\)
- `now\wil` - Present without future
- `you\was` - Self without past
- `rem\for` - Remembering without forgetting
- `wil\fer` - Future without fear

### Superposition (±)
- `was±now±wil` - All three tenses together
- `her±gon` - Here and gone both
- `beg±now±end` - Origin, presence, conclusion unified

### Conditional (:)
- `tim:con` - Time given context
- `tim:sel` - Time given consciousness

